UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2326
1 or sportswomen of each respective district.
2 (b) When the term of a member expires, the commissioner shall call a meeting of
3 the sportsmen and sportswomen in that district not later than thirty (30) days
4 prior to the expiration of the member's term. Notice of the meeting shall be
5 given by publication pursuant to KRS Chapter 424.
6 (c) At the meeting, the sportsmen or sportswomen in attendance shall select and
7 submit to the Governor a list of five (5) residents and citizens of the district,
8 each of whom:[ who]
9 1. Is either an experienced hunter, angler, trapper, farmer, or biologist;
10 2. Has[have] held a hunting and fishing license[licenses] in Kentucky or
11 another state for at least the previous five (5) consecutive years;[, or
12 who have been hunting and fishing in the Commonwealth for the
13 previous five (5) consecutive years while license-exempt under KRS
14 150.170, and who]
15 3. Is[Are] well informed on the subject of wildlife conservation and
16 restoration, including the North American Model of Wildlife
17 Conservation; and
18 4. Has an active membership in a conservation or sportsman's or
19 sportswoman's organization in the Commonwealth.
20 (d) Each sportsman or sportswomen may vote for one (1) candidate only, and the
21 list submitted to the Governor shall be made up of the names of the five (5)
22 candidates receiving the five (5) highest vote totals.
23 (e)[(d)] The Governor shall appoint a successor to the member whose term has
24 expired no later than January 20 of the year following the year in which the
25 member's term expired.
26 (f) Upon appointment by the Governor, each appointee to the commission shall
27 file with the Secretary of State an affidavit, duly signed and sworn, setting
Page 2 of 7
XXXX 3/2/2026 8:16 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2326
1 forth in detail how he or she complies with qualifications and requirements
2 of this section.
3 (g) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the Senate shall not
4 consider any legislation confirming the appointment or reappointment of a
5 member of the commission unless:
6 (a) The legislation has been referred to the Senate standing committee of
7 jurisdiction as determined by the Senate Committee on Committees;
8 (b) A meeting of the Senate standing committee to which the legislation
9 was referred has been held to determine the qualifications of the
10 nominee and to review the affidavit required under paragraph (f) of
11 this subsection; and
12 (c) The legislation has been reported favorably by the Senate standing
13 committee.
14 (4) Upon appointment to the Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources Commission,
15 each member of the commission[commissioner] shall execute a bond of one
16 thousand dollars ($1,000) in favor of the Department of Fish and Wildlife
17 Resources, the premium on this bond to be paid out of department funds.
18 (5) In the event of vacancies other than by expiration, the Governor shall fill the
19 vacancy for the unexpired part of the term from the names remaining on the list
20 previously submitted for the district from which the vacancy arose. An appointee
21 chosen under this subsection shall not serve on the commission until duly
22 confirmed by the Senate.
23 (6) Each member of the commission shall take the constitutional oath of office.
24 (7) The Governor shall remove any member of the commission for cause under
25 subsection (2) of this section and may remove a member of the commission for
26 nonfeasance, neglect of duty, or misconduct in office; but shall first deliver to the
27 member a copy of all charges in writing and afford to him or her an opportunity for
Page 3 of 7
XXXX 3/2/2026 8:16 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2326
1 an administrative hearing to be conducted in accordance with KRS Chapter 13B.
2 (8) Each member of the commission shall be entitled to reimbursement for actual and
3 necessary traveling and other expenses incurred by him or her in the discharge of
4 his or her official duties and to be paid from the game and fish fund.
5 (9) A majority of the commission shall constitute a quorum for the transaction of any
6 business, for the performance of any duty or for the exercise of any power vested in
7 the commission.
8 (10) The department shall have its principal office in Franklin County, and is authorized
9 to purchase all supplies, equipment, and printed forms and to issue any notices and
10 publications as the commissioner may deem necessary to carry out the provisions of
11 this chapter.
12 (11) Within one (1) year of his or her initial appointment to the commission, a
13 commission member shall complete six (6) hours of executive branch ethics
14 training conducted by the Executive Branch Ethics Commission established
15 under KRS Chapter 11A. Each commission member shall complete three (3)
16 hours of executive branch ethics training each year that he or she serves on the
17 commission thereafter. Current commission members shall complete their initial
18 six (6) hours of executive branch ethics training within one (1) year after the
19 effective date of this Act.
20 (12) The word "sportsman" or "sportswoman" as used in this section shall mean a
21 resident hunter or fisherman or fisherwoman who has been licensed in Kentucky
22 for each of the past two (2) consecutive years.
23 Section 2. KRS 150.061 is amended to read as follows:
24 (1) (a) Notwithstanding any provisions of KRS Chapter 18A, 42, 45, 45A, 56, or 64
25 to the contrary, the commission shall have the sole authority to appoint a
26 commissioner of the Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources, who shall be
27 a person:
Page 4 of 7
XXXX 3/2/2026 8:16 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2326
1 1. With knowledge of and experience in the requirements for the
2 protection, conservation and restoration of the wildlife resources of the
3 Commonwealth;[state]
4 2. Who has demonstrated active participation in hunting, fishing, or both
5 for ten (10) years prior to appointment;
6 3. Who has held a hunting and fishing license in Kentucky or another
7 state for at least the previous three (3) consecutive years; and
8 4. Who has not served on the Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources
9 Commission for at least three (3) years.
10 (b) The commission shall be the sole contracting body for the purposes of KRS
11 Chapter 45A and shall submit any proposed personal service contract with a
12 commissioner to the Government Contact Review Committee for its review
13 pursuant to KRS 45A.690 to 45A.725. The commissioner shall serve for a
14 defined employment contract term not to exceed four (4) years and shall be
15 subject to:
16 1.[(a)] Annual review by the commission in closed, executive session;
17 2.[(b)] Removal by the commission for the same cause and in the same
18 manner in which the Governor may remove a member of the
19 commission;[ and]
20 3.[(c)] Reappointment by the commission; and
21 4. Confirmation by the Senate.
22 (2) For commissioner vacancies that occur after the effective date of this Act, the
23 commission shall conduct a national search to identify the best qualified
24 individual to hold the position and carry out the requirements of this chapter.
25 (3) The commissioner shall receive such compensation as the commission may solely
26 determine, and shall be reimbursed for all actual and necessary travel and other
27 expenses incurred by him or her in the performance of his or her official duties.
Page 5 of 7
