UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2326
1 (4)[(3)] Before entering upon the duties of his or her office, the commissioner shall
2 take and subscribe to the constitutional oath of office, and shall, in addition thereto,
3 swear or affirm that he or she holds no other public office, nor any position upon or
4 under any political committee or party. Upon appointment by the commission, the
5 commissioner shall execute a bond of five thousand dollars ($5,000) in favor of the
6 Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources, the premium on said bond to be paid
7 out of department funds.
8 (5)[(4)] Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the commissioner shall
9 be the sole appointing authority for the department for the purposes of KRS Chapter
10 18A and shall have general supervision and control of all activities, functions,
11 appointments, and employees of the department. He or she shall enforce all
12 provisions of the laws of the state relating to wild animals, birds, fish and
13 amphibians, and shall exercise all powers necessarily incident thereto not
14 specifically conferred on the commission. The commissioner shall make an annual
15 report of all receipts and disbursements and file same with the Secretary of State of
16 the Commonwealth of Kentucky.
17 (6)[(5)] If federal or other grant funds become available to pay their salaries, the
18 commissioner may appoint and employ other persons that he or she may deem
19 necessary or desirable to accomplish the purposes of this chapter. The
20 commissioner shall determine the compensation, duties, and terms of employment
21 of these employees, and grant funded, time-limited positions shall be approved by
22 the commission as needed. Employees whose salaries are funded through federal or
23 other grant funds shall not be counted in any tally of permanent employees made
24 for employee cap or budgetary purposes.
25 Section 3. Whereas it is critical that that the changes to the qualifications for the
26 members of the Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources Commission and the
27 commissioner be enacted as soon as possible to apply to any new vacancies that may
